article.headline: Massachusetts 83, Marist 68
article.story: UNCASVILLE, Conn. (AP) -- Chris Lowe scored a career-high 23 points and Gary Forbes added 18 points and 11 rebounds to help Massachusetts defeat Marist 83-68 on Saturday night. Ricky Harris added 18 points for Massachusetts (6-2), which outscored the Red Foxes 31-10 in the final 8:30 to snap Marist's five-game win streak. Louie McCroskey led Marist (6-4) with 22 points. Jay Gavin had 12. The game was tied at 32 at intermission. Marist took its largest lead of the game at 58-52 with 8:15 left in the game on a Spongy Benjamin lay-up. Harris tied the game at 58-58 with 6:36 left when he converted a driving lay-up off a Lowe steal, and the Minutemen retook the lead 30 seconds later when Forbes converted the fourth of four straight free throws. Etienne Brower's 3-pointer with 3:39 left gave Massachusetts a 70-60 lead, capping an 18-2 run.
